<p><i><b>Love and Rockets</b></i> (often abbreviated <i><b>L&amp;R</b></i>) is a black and white <a href="/wiki/Comic_book" title="Comic book">comic book</a> series by <a href="/wiki/Gilbert_Hernandez" title="Gilbert Hernandez">Gilbert Hernandez</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jaime_Hernandez" title="Jaime Hernandez">Jaime Hernandez</a>, sometimes cited jointly as Los Bros Hernandez. Their brother <a href="/wiki/Mario_Hernandez" title="Mario Hernandez">Mario Hernandez</a> is an occasional contributor. It was one of the first comics in the <a href="/wiki/Alternative_comics" title="Alternative comics">alternative comics</a> revolution of the <a href="/wiki/1980s_in_comics" title="1980s in comics">1980s</a>.</p>
